      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "> Any idea how your block estimator ended up giving you estimates lower than your set min mempool feerate? Seems to me this requires you to change your min rate _after_ your estimator builds these estimates?\r\n\r\n@instagibbs: As I understand it, the fee estimator in Bitcoin Core uses statistical analysis of previous transaction confirmation times to build up its estimates. The `mempoolminfee` reacts to current mempool conditions.\r\n\r\nSuppose that there is a sudden spike in transaction traffic. Fees had been low for a while; the mempool had been close to empty. Suddenly, someone drops a million transactions onto the network. This will have no immediate effect on Bitcoin Core's fee estimator (sadly), but it will absolutely bump up `mempoolminfee` immediately.",
      "created_at" : "2020-08-31T16:02:15Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/19699#issuecomment-683871972",
